        "description": "<p>Your users often leave long comments or copy long text to your comments and hide important comments.<br />\nIf you are using standard wordpress comments system, this plugin can limit the maximum comments length to 1500 characters.</p>\n<h4>Demo</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://rentrating.net/review/australia/queensland/kangaroo-point/19-castlebar-st-kangaroo-point-queensland-australia/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Demo</a>.</p>\n<h4>Social Media</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/rentrating\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Like Us</a> on Facebook and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/RentRatingNET\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Follow Us</a> on Twitter.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Go to plugins in your dashboard and select &#8216;add new&#8217;</li>\n<li>Search for &#8216;Maximum Comment Length to 1500&#8217; </li>\n<li>Click &#8216;Install Now&#8217; and then activate the plugin</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "<p>Our support forum is available on <a href=\"https://rentrating.net/forums/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">support</a> website.</p>\n\n<h4>Installation Instructions</h4>\n<p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to plugins in your dashboard and select &#8216;add new&#8217;</li>\n<li>Search for &#8216;Maximum Comment Length to 1500&#8217; </li>\n<li>Click &#8216;Install Now&#8217; and then activate the plugin</li>\n</ol>\n</p>\n\n",
